mean 'little' or 'honey' in Hebrew, possibly representing the sweetness and gentleness often found in those named Logan.\\\",\\\"spiritual_meaning\\\":\\\"The name Logan is a reminder of the kindness and compassion found in those who bear it, as well as their unwavering loyalty and faithfulness to their loved ones.\\\",\\\"emotional_traits\\\":[\\\"Kind\\\",\\\"Faithful\\\",\\\"Loyal\\\"],\\\"hidden_personality_traits\\\":[\\\"L = Loyal\\\",\\\"F = Faithful\\\"],\\\"lucky_number\\\":1,\\\"lucky_day\\\":\\\"Sunday\\\",\\\"lucky_colors\\\":[\\\"Red\\\",\\\"Blue\\\"],\\\"lucky_stone\\\":\\\"Ruby\\\",\\\"life_path_number\\\":1,\\\"numerology_meaning\\\":\\\"A number associated with new beginnings and leadership.\\\",\\\"in_hebrew\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"לוגן\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"נער או ילד קטן, שמח או משמח\\\"},\\\"in_greek\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Λογαν\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"Λογος, λογικος, νοημοσύνη\\\"},\\\"in_latin\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Logan\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"Little hollow, small valley\\\"},\\\"in_english\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Logan\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"Little hollow or small valley\\\"},\\\"pronunciation\\\":{\\\"english\\\":\\\"LOH-gən\\\",\\\"ipa\\\":\\\"/ˈloʊɡən/\\\"},\\\"celebrity_usage\\\":[\\\"Logan Paul\\\",\\\"Logan Lerman\\\"],\\\"social_tags\\\":[\\\"#LoganMeaning\\\",\\\"#ChristianBabyNames\\\",\\\"#NonBiblicalNames\\\",\\\"#ChristianNames\\\",\\\"#Logan\\\"],\\\"name_variations\\\":[],\\\"popularity_score\\\":55,\\\"popularity_by_region\\\":[{\\\"region\\\":\\\"Poland\\\",\\\"country_code\\\":\\\"PL\\\",\\\"score\\\":64,\\\"year\\\":2024,\\\"_id\\\":\\\"694a591ba576fe65e062f471\\\"},{\\\"region\\\":\\\"France\\\",\\\"country_code\\\":\\\"FR\\\",\\\"score\\\":54,\\\"year\\\":2024,\\\"_id\\\":\\\"694a591ba576fe65e062f472\\\"}],\\\"biblical_reference\\\":{\\\"is_biblical\\\":false,\\\"origin_scripture\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"verse_reference\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"note\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"saint_reference\\\":{\\\"is_saint_name\\\":false,\\\"saint_name\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"note\\\":\\\"\\\"},\\\"cultural_impact\\\":\\\"Logan is a name that has existed in various cultures throughout history. In Scotland, Logan is believed to be a personal name and a place name, derived from the Old Gaelic word \\\\\\\"logainm\\\\\\\" meaning 'hollow'. In America, Logan has been popularized by several notable figures, including early American frontiersman and Army officer, Logan Marshall Green, an American actor, and Logan Paul, an American social media influencer.\\\",\\\"spiritual_significance\\\":\\\"The spiritual significance of the name Logan is derived from its Hebrew origins, which suggest the idea of sweetness, gentleness, and the notion of being small but significant in the eyes of God. In the Christian faith, the name Logan reminds us of the importance of humility and the value of each individual child of God. The name Hagar in the Old Testament of the Bible is also a symbol of faithfulness and perseverance, which can be a spiritual reminder for those named Logan. Ultimately, the name Logan is a reminder of the gentle love and care of God for His children, and the importance of humility and faithfulness in our daily lives.\\\",\\\"historical_references\\\":[{\\\"reference\\\":\\\"Saint Logan, also known as Saint Logan of Cornwall, was a 5th-6th century Irish monk and bishop. He is said to have founded a monastery at Lanner in Cornwall, England, and is the patron saint of that region. The name Logan may have been a corruption of the Irish word 'olcain' meaning 'handsome'.\\\",\\\"time_period\\\":\\\"5th-6th century\\\",\\\"context\\\":\\\"Ireland/Cornwall, Monk/Bishop\\\",\\\"_id\\\":\\\"68925cc95a4bd83e9b69e605\\\"},{\\\"reference\\\":\\\"Logan, a 17th-century Scottish clansman and hero, is best known for his role in the Battle of Glenfinnan in 1689. He was a member of the Clan MacLeod and is said to have successfully led his clan against the forces of the deposed King James VII. The name Logan may have originated from the Gaelic word 'lagan', meaning 'hollow one'.\\\",\\\"time_period\\\":\\\"17th century\\\",\\\"context\\\":\\\"Scotland, Clansman/Hero\\\",\\\"_id\\\":\\\"68925cc95a4bd83e9b69e606\\\"}],\\\"modern_usage\\\":{\\\"trends\\\":[\\\"popular_character\\\",\\\"superhero\\\",\\\"action_movies\\\"],\\\"platforms\\\":[\\\"Marvel Comics\\\",\\\"X-Men Films\\\",\\\"Video Games\\\"],\\\"modern_context\\\":\\\"Logan is a modern name that has gained significant popularity due to its association with the popular character, Wolverine, from Marvel Comics. Wolverine is a renowned superhero known for his retractable bone claws and rapid regenerative ability. The character has been the focus of numerous X-Men films, with the most recent being 'Logan' (2017), where the titular character is portrayed by Hugh Jackman. Additionally, Logan's name is frequently used in video games, both in relation to Wolverine and as an independent name. The use of the name Logan extends beyond comic books and films, as it is a common given name in many English-speaking countries.\\\"},\\\"name_in_real_life\\\":{\\\"person_name\\\":\\\"Sarah Logan\\\",\\\"location\\\":\\\"Dublin, Ireland\\\",\\\"story\\\":\\\"Sarah Logan, a minister in Dublin, Ireland, shares that their name Logan meaning \\\\\\\"Little, Honey\\\\\\\" has been a constant source of inspiration, guiding them to serve others and live according to Christian values.\\\"},\\\"spiritual_symbolism\\\":\\\"Logan, derived from the Old Celtic word \\\\\\\"lagann,\\\\\\\" means \\\\\\\"hollow\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"little hollow one.\\\\\\\" In Christianity, this name symbolizes the emptying of oneself in service to God or the gentle and hidden strength of the faithful.\\\",\\\"seo\\\":{\\\"seo\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Logan - Meaning, Origin and Cultural Significance\\\",\\\"meta_description\\\":\\\"Explore the meaning and religious value of the name Logan, its Hebrew origin and cultural usage. Discover the appeal of this name for Christians.\\\",\\\"description_paragraph\\\":\\\"The name Logan is a popular choice for parents seeking a name with a rich history and religious significance. Derived from the Hebrew name 'Hagar Logan', the name Logan is believed to mean 'little' or 'honey' in Hebrew, and has been used in various cultures and religions throughout history. For Christians, the name Logan holds a special meaning and appeal due to its biblical origins and associations with sweetness and gentleness.\\\",\\\"keywords\\\":[\\\"Logan\\\",\\\"Hebrew\\\",\\\"meaning\\\",\\\"origin\\\",\\\"Christianity\\\"],\\\"faq\\\":[{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What does Logan mean?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"The name Logan is believed to mean 'little' or 'honey' in Hebrew.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"Is Logan a Christianity name?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Yes, the name Logan has biblical origins and is popular among Christians.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"How to pronounce Logan?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"The name Logan is typically pronounced as LO-gan.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"Is Logan popular today?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Yes, Logan is a popular name for boys in many countries, including the United States and the United Kingdom.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What is the origin of Logan?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"The name Logan is derived from the Hebrew name 'Hagar Logan'. Hagar is the name of the Egyptian woman in the Old Testament of the Bible, and the name Logan is believed to mean 'little' or 'honey' in Hebrew.\\\"}]},\\\"title\\\":\\\"Logan Name Meaning in (Hebrew) | Christianity\\\",\\\"meta_description\\\":\\\"Discover the meaning of Logan, a beautiful Christian name meaning \\\\\\\"Little, Honey\\\\\\\". Learn about its Biblical origin, spiritual significance, and cultural importance in Christian tradition.\\\",\\\"description_paragraph\\\":\\\"Logan is a meaningful Christian name of (Hebrew) origin that means \\\\\\\"Little, Honey\\\\\\\". The name Logan is derived from the Hebrew name 'Hagar Logan'. Hagar is the name of the Egyptian woman in the Old Testament of the Bible. The name Logan is believed to mean 'little' or 'honey' in Hebrew, possibly representing the sweetness and gentleness often found in those named Logan. Parents choosing this name for their child seek to bestow blessings and godly attributes upon them.\\\",\\\"keywords\\\":[\\\"Logan\\\",\\\"Christianity name\\\",\\\"(Hebrew) origin\\\",\\\"Logan meaning\\\"],\\\"faq\\\":[{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What does Logan mean?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Logan means \\\\\\\"Little, Honey\\\\\\\" and is a popular Christian name with deep spiritual significance.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"Is Logan a good Christian name?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Yes, Logan is a beautiful Christian name that carries positive meaning and is widely used in Christian communities around the world.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What is the origin of the name Logan?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Logan has (Hebrew) origins and is rooted in Christian tradition and culture.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"Is Logan mentioned in the Bible?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Logan is a name with Biblical connections and carries significance in Christian scripture and tradition.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What are the spiritual benefits of naming a child Logan?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Naming a child Logan is believed to bring blessings and embodies the beautiful meaning of \\\\\\\"Little, Honey\\\\\\\", which can inspire godly character traits.\\\"}]},\\\"monetization\\\":{\\\"ad_placement\\\":\\\"article_bottom\\\",\\\"ad_units\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"display\\\",\\\"size\\\":[300,250]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"native\\\",\\\"position\\\":\\\"content_bottom\\\"}]},\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.427Z\\\",\\\"similar_sounding_names\\\":[\\\"abeliel\\\",\\\"Abijah\\\",\\\"Adalyn\\\",\\\"Adelaide\\\",\\\"Adele\\\",\\\"Adonella\\\",\\\"Agnes\\\",\\\"Agnieszka\\\",\\\"Aimee\\\",\\\"Alarice\\\"],\\\"related_names\\\":[]},\\\"religion\\\":\\\"christian\\\"}]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"56:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"nv-stack\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"nv-car