center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$5b:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:children:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-shield h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Cultural Context\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Cultural Significance\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":\"Logan is a name that has existed in various cultures throughout history. In Scotland, Logan is believed to be a personal name and a place name, derived from the Old Gaelic word \\\"logainm\\\" meaning 'hollow'. In America, Logan has been popularized by several notable figures, including early American frontiersman and Army officer, Logan Marshall Green, an American actor, and Logan Paul, an American social media influencer.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":\"The spiritual significance of the name Logan is derived from its Hebrew origins, which suggest the idea of sweetness, gentleness, and the notion of being small but significant in the eyes of God. In the Christian faith, the name Logan reminds us of the importance of humility and the value of each individual child of God. The name Hagar in the Old Testament of the Bible is also a symbol of faithfulness and perseverance, which can be a spiritual reminder for those named Logan. Ultimately, the name Logan is a reminder of the gentle love and care of God for His children, and the importance of humility and faithfulness in our daily lives.\"}],\"$undefined\",\"$undefined\",false,false]}]]}]\n60:[\"$\",\"$L70\",null,{\"className\":\"my-6\",\"minHeight\":\"90px\",\"instanceId\":\"name-detail-mid\"}]\n61:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$57:props:children:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-clock h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Historical Usage\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Historical References\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"Saint Logan, also known as Saint Logan of Cornwall, was a 5th-6th century Irish monk and bishop. He is said to have founded a monastery at Lanner in Cornwall, England, and is the patron saint of that region. The name Logan may have been a corruption of the Irish word 'olcain' meaning 'handsome'.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"5th-6th century\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"Logan, a 17th-century Scottish clansman and hero, is best known for his role in the Battle of Glenfinnan in 1689. He was a member of the Clan MacLeod and is said to have successfully led his clan against the forces of the deposed King James VII. The name Logan may have originated from the Gaelic word 'lagan', meaning 'hollow one'.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"17th century\"}]]}]]}]]}]\n62:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$5c:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:children:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-sparkles h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Spiritual\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Spiritual Symbolism\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\",\"children\":\"Logan, derived from the Old Celtic word \\\"lagann,\\\" means \\\"hollow\\\" or \\\"little hollow one.\\\" In Christianity, this name symbolizes the emptying of oneself in service to God or the gentle and hidden strength of the faithful.\"}]]}]\n63:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L1a\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":[[\"path\",{\"d\":\"M16 7h6v6\",\"key\":\"box55l\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\",\"key\":\"1t1m79\"}]],\"className\":\"lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\"}]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-x